snippet.title: First Place | The Feature Film
snippet.description:
TikTok is in shambles as all eyes are on St Gabriel’s High School after their Samoan group went full flop era at Polyfest.

Victoria’s on her comeback szn energy for 2025, but things are not giving. She’s heartbroken, her squad is basically a lucky dip, and Leone, the rival taupou, is out to snatch her crown 👑🔥

Cue the drama: egos clash, friendships fumble, and baby oil is literally flying as the group grinds for redemption.

Who’s got what it takes to lead the group? Who will be crowned taupou? And what does First Place really mean?

FIRST PLACE is a wild ride through heartbreak, hustle, and hallways — a love letter to siva Samoa, school pride, and all the chaos of teenage life 💃🏽📚😭

With a stacked cast of fresh faces and iconic Pasifika faves, and made entirely by a Pasifika crew, this show’s a full-on tribute to the legacy of ASB Polyfest, the biggest Pasifika dance fest on the planet, and the generations who’ve made it what it is.

This is their story.


Directed by Damon Fepuleai with Bianca Seinafo Tuilaepa
Produced by Eileen Lee, Hope Papalii
Written by Bianca Seinafo Tuilaepa and Mario Faumui with additions from Leki Jackson Bourke. 

*Watch the ASB POLYFEST 2025 Livestream here: https://www.asbpolyfest.co.nz/p/4482-watch-live

In Honour of Melegalenuu Ah Sam
Queen of Polyfest Samoan stage 1993 - 2024
Your legacy always remembered.

snippet.title: She Was Scared When He Blocked Her… But It Was A Beautiful Act Of Kindness #shorts
snippet.description:
She was just driving down the road when a tow truck suddenly blocked her way. Her heart raced as the driver stepped out and walked toward her. But instead of danger, he handed her something she didn’t even know was missing — her wallet, left on the roof. A simple act of kindness turned a moment of fear into something unforgettable.
Watch till the end — it will touch your heart!
